description: Succinate dehydrogenase [ubiquinone] cytochrome b small subunit, mitochondrial (CybS), also known as CII-4 or QPs3 or Succinate dehydrogenase complex subunit D or Succinate-ubiquinone oxidoreductase cytochrome b small subunit or Succinate-ubiquinone reductase membrane anchor subunit, and encoded by the gene name SDHD or SD14, is one of four proteins that make up the tricarboxylic cycle enzyme succinate dehydrogenase (SCH).
name: Anti-SDHD Antibody
